These paragraphs empower the Court to make the following orders:


 (a) an order quashing or setting aside the decision, or a part of the decision, with effect from the date of the order or from such earlier or later date as the court specifies;

 (b) an order referring the matter to which the decision relates to the person who made the decision for further consideration, subject to such directions as the court thinks fit;



46 If the applicant succeeds in this proceeding the applicant will not thereby be entitled to resume his employment.

