67 Williams J then referred to Dixon J's dicta in Nette v Howarth [1935] HCA 22 ; 53 CLR 55 cited above and said (at 315):
 These and other cases cited to us establish that the question whether any part and if so what part of the personal earnings of a bankrupt vests in the official receiver as after-acquired property is really academic.
